notesStmt.note: Title of main text from colophon (f. 336v); other titles from caption titles.

1. f. 1v-4r: Farāʼid al-fawāʼid li-taḥqīq maʻānī al-istiʻārah -- 2. f. 4v-31v: Kitāb al-nāsikh wa-al-mansūkh -- 3. f. 32r-33v : Risālah-i Mullā Zāhirī -- 4. f. 36v-336v: al-Tawḍīḥ -- 5. f. 337v-338v: [Notes]
Description from auction catalog, number 362, tipped in before front flyleaf; note in pencil on clipping, "Carnegie Cat 334, June 1973".

msContents.summary: A copy of the Tawḍīḥ, which is a commentary on another work by al-Maḥbūbī called Tanqīḥ al-uṣūl; three other, shorter works are also included: on metaphor, on abbrogated verses and one poem in Persian.

supportDesc.extent: i, 338 leaves : 248 x 142 (185 x 85) mm, bound to 256 x 152 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 15-19 long lines; partially border-ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink, pointed.

binding.p: Lacquered boards with floral center and text in the border; insides are gold floral designs on a black ground.

origin.p: Long work is dated Ramadan 1241 A.H. (1826 CE) (f. 336v) and each shorter work is dated 1242 A.H. (1827 CE).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by ʻAbd al-Ghafūr, "This Koran was taken from the library of Abdul Gafur in May 1880 by the column under command of Major General John Ross C.B." [signed] Eden Morton Lt. Col. (f. 338v).
Formerly owned by Eden Morton, "A present from Subadar Major Nutha Singh 23rd Pioneers" (signature and note, first flyleaf recto at front of book)
